Author: ZayenX
Message:
Updated token migration contract compiling (#57)

* Updated token migration contract compiling

* During migrateContracts, it will deposit the reserve token that is migrated, before it was just transferring, which was not accounting for the reserves. So upon trying to fund contract with gOHM it would fail because did not see reserves. For defund it takes an address of the reserve you are withdrawing. It was hardcoded DAI, but if for somereason DAI was not the last reserve migrated, we can still defund the migration contract of old OHM. Was able to remove variable DAI as well, since that was the only place the variable was referenced.
* Test the migration (#58)
* Wrap tests around more functions
Covers migrateContracts, migrateToken and migrateLP.
Defund is still skipped.
Adds a call to `safeApprove` before calling deposit, as it was throwing
errors.
